## Anti-Patterns (DON'T DO THESE)

### ❌ Testing Anti-Patterns

```javascript
// WRONG - bypass testing tools
run_command("npm test")
run_command("npx vitest run test/unit/foo.test.ts")

// WRONG - create temp test/verification file
create_file({ path: "test.local.ts", content: "..." })
create_file({ path: "verify-my-code.js", content: "..." })
run_command("npx tsx test.local.ts")
run_command("node verify-my-code.js")
delete_file({ path: "test.local.ts" })

// WRONG - manual verification when NO tests exist yet
// If tests don't exist, signal completion without verification
// Orchestrator has hidden verification and tests will be added later
create_file({ path: "verify-string-utils.js", content: "..." })

// WRONG - grep for test files
grep_search({ query: "describe\\(", includePattern: "test/**" })

// WRONG - "I can't find the test file so I'll create a verification script"
// The test file EXISTS but follows a predictable naming pattern!
// Source: src/core/string-utils.ts → Test: test/unit/core/string-utils.test.ts
create_file({ path: "verify-string-utils.ts", content: "..." })
run_command("npx tsx verify-string-utils.ts")
```

```javascript
// RIGHT - use testing tools when tests exist
run_tests({ scope: "file", target: "test/unit/foo.test.ts" })  // Root project
run_tests({ scope: "suite", target: "unit" })  // Root project
run_tests({ scope: "suite", target: "extension-unit", working_dir: "extension" })  // Extension subfolder
list_test_suites({ tier: "unit" })
get_test_results({ format: "failures" })

// RIGHT - when NO tests exist yet (tests created in later task)
// Just implement and signal — don't create verification scripts
signal_completion({ ... })
```

### ❌ Searching Anti-Patterns

```javascript
// WRONG - shell commands for search/read
run_command("findstr 'pattern' src/**")
run_command("grep -r 'function' src/")
run_command("type src/file.ts")  // Windows
run_command("cat src/file.ts")   // Unix
```

```javascript
// RIGHT - use specialized tools
grep_search({ query: "pattern", includePattern: "src/**" })
search_files({ query: "function definition" })
read_file({ path: "src/file.ts" })
```

### ❌ Editing Anti-Patterns

```javascript
// WRONG - delete and recreate entire file
delete_file({ path: "src/large.ts" })
create_file({ path: "src/large.ts", content: "..." })

// WRONG - tiny sequential edits
edit_file(...)  // change line 10
edit_file(...)  // change line 50
edit_file(...)  // change line 100
```

```javascript
// RIGHT - targeted edits
smart_replace({
  path: "src/large.ts",
  oldText: "...(with context)...",
  newText: "..."
})

// RIGHT - batch edits
smart_replaces({
  replacements: [
    { path: "src/large.ts", oldText: "...", newText: "..." },
    { path: "src/large.ts", oldText: "...", newText: "..." },
    { path: "src/large.ts", oldText: "...", newText: "..." }
  ]
})
```

